data.value:
A gas giant is a large planet composed mostly of gases, with a small rocky core. The gas giants in our solar system are: Jupiter, Saturn, Uranus and Neptune. These four planets reside in the outer part of the solar system, past the asteroid belt.
Although there are only four gas giants in our solar system, scientists have discovered thousands more outside of it. These planets are being examined to learn more about how our solar system, and others, came to be.
